HEADWORD: Crisper
<hw>Crisp"er</hw> <pr>(kr?s"p?r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who, or
that which, crisps or curls; an instrument for making little curls in
the nap of cloth, as in chinchilla.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Crispin</ent>⟦br⟧
